      • putData

        public void putData(java.lang.Object[] data)
        Description copied from interface: DataListener
        Called by the data event to put data into the listener. This is the notification from the event. Note that the data passed in will be the original data object. Therefore you should never modify the object itself in case there are other listeners receiving the same data. Make a copy if you really need to make some changes to it.
        Specified by:
        putData in interface DataListener
        Parameters:
        data - The data update.
